Interface Headers<T>

        Long getTimeMillisAndRemove(T name)
        Returns and removes the date value of a header with the specified name as milliseconds. If there are more than one values for the specified name, the first value is returned.
        Parameters:
        name - The name of the header to search
        Returns:
        the first header value in milliseconds if the header is found and its value is a date. null if there's no such header or its value is not a date.
